args: Botan is visiting a village after receiving\na request for assistance...
So you want me to find your cat?
Yes! Her name's Mewmew, and she's a\nlittle cutie with gray fur and stripes.
She went off into the woods and hasn't\ncome back. I want to go look for her,\nbut these old feet don't work so well.
Oh! It's a cat with gray stripes!\nAre you Mewmew?
Aw, man! Now she's hiding again.
...Anyway, she ran off and hid and now\nI can't find her. Got any bright ideas?
Why don't I help ya?! I've got plenty of\nexperience kitty huntin'.
That is...not something I expected you\nto say. But sure, I'd love some help.
First, yer gonna need some treats.
Keep yer head low, yeah?!\nDon't want this furball to spot ya.
I can smell your kitty snacks from here.\nIs the stench ever going to come off?
The stronger the smell, the easier it is\nto attract a cat. And speakin' of, look!
Yes! She's eating 'em! Now let's catchâ€”
Wait! Don't move. All we're doin' today\nis givin' her a couple'a snacks.
Cats are cautious. Ya gotta keep stuffin'\nthe little critters with treats if ya wanna\nmake 'em drop their guard.
Uuuugh! That's sooooo tedious!\nLet's just catch her right now!
And what happens if ya mess it up?\nWe'll never find her then.
A warrior must strike while the iron is hot!
Look, yer eager. I get it.\nAnd that ain't necessarily bad.
But there's a fine line between eager\nand impatient, yeah?
Ugh! Fine, we'll do it your stupid way.\nSo how long do we feed her, then?
Four or five days should do the trick.\nJust gotta be patient!
Hey there, kitty. Still hungry, eh?
Now we move juuuust a bit closer so\nshe can get a little more used to us.
Look! She's totally used to us now!\nLet's throw a bag over her and take\nher back while she's distracted!
She might look relaxed, but she ain't.\nWe're just gonna sit and watch.
Okay, she's rolling over on her back.\nWe HAVE to snag her now!
Nope. That's a trick. If we try'n snag her,\nshe'll bolt like a shot and all of our\nhard work will be for nothin'.
Okay, this is just stupid. She's ASLEEP!\nWe HAVE to grab her now!
Cats sleep with one eye open, yeah?\nJust a little longer now. Be patient.
Whoa, whoa! Please tell me ya ain't just\ngonna leap outta the bushes and try to\nsnag her!
No, Ranzal. I'm not. I've been patient\nthis long, so a little more won't hurt.
The poor owner's probably\nworried sick about this little thingâ€”\nbe a real shame to screw it up now.
Hey kitty! We're your friends!\nYeah, that's a good kitty...
Hot pot of coffee! It's a fiend!
Stay away from Mewmew, jerk! Haaaah!
DANGIT! DANGIT TO HECK!\n*sigh* I'm sorry, Ranzal.
Skip the apologies. This ain't yer fault.
We're never going to earn her trust back.

It's because ya didn't chase her all over
hell and breakfast. Cats are smart enough
to know the difference between friend
and fiend, after all.
Ya saved her, and she knows it.
Okay then, Mewmew. Let's go home.
